## Summary

**What changed:** Added a 4-line `eprintln!` progress indicator in `read_events_bounded` at `src/state.rs:3275-3278`. 

**Where:** The `else` branch (sampling path) — after deciding `total_lines > limit`, before the blocking `Vec<&str>` collection. When the file is small (fast path), no message is emitted to avoid noise.

**Verification:**
• `cargo fmt -- --check`: ✅ passed
• `cargo build`: ✅ passed
• `cargo test read_events_bounded -- --test-threads=1`: ✅ all 9 tests passed
• End-to-end: `state why last-failure` works correctly (CI's 173 events take the fast path, so no progress message — expected behavior for small files per the fallback)

**How it works:** When a user runs `yyds state why last-failure` against a 50K+ event log, they'll now see `reading 100000 state events (sampling last 100000 of 52300 lines)...` on stderr before the blocking read. This converts an anxiety-inducing silence into a predictable wait.

